g collection of archaeological material. The collection ranges from Siracusa and the surrounding territory (Megara Hyblaia, Akrai, Kasmenai etc) to encompass all of eastern Sicily, reaching as far as Gela and Agrigento. The ground floor covers prehistory through to the end of the Classical period. Upstairs includes Hellenistic and Roman Syracuse and a display of material from the catacombs. A gallery displaying material from Hellenistic eastern Sicily is in preparation.",{"settlement":86,"region":86,"country":123,"address":124,"geo":125},"Italy","Viale Teocrito 66, 96100 - Siracusa",{"lat":126,"lon":127},37.07636989,15.2866213,{"_":129,"mainLang":130,"languages":131},"Ancient Greek","grc",[129],{"type":133,"bibl":134},"edition",[135,147],{"type":136,"n":137,"citedRange":138,"ptr":139,"ref":140,"title":141,"author":142,"date":143,"citation":144,"uri":145,"year":146},"bulletin","SEG","49.1331.7",{"target":140},"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/F2GG87EQ","Supplementum epigraphicum graecum","","1923-","\u003Cspan>‘Supplementum Epigraphicum Graecum’, \u003Ci>Supplementum Epigraphicum Graecum\u003C/i>, 1923, \u003Ca href=\"http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/1607583\">http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/1607583\u003C/a>\u003C/span>","https://www.zotero.org/groups/isicily/items/F2GG87EQ","1923",{"author":148,"date":149,"citedRange":150,"ptr":151,"ref":152,"inscriptionDate":149,"title":153,"citation":154,"uri":155,"year":149},"Manganaro","1999","68-69 no.64 fig.146",{"target":152},"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/GRB3IPD5","Sikelika: studi di antichità e di epigrafia della Sicilia greca","\u003Cspan>Giacomo Manganaro, \u003Ci>Sikelika: studi di antichità e di epigrafia della Sicilia greca\u003C/i>, Biblioteca di QUCC 8 (Pisa, Roma: Istituti Editoriali e Poligrafici internazionali, 1999)\u003C/span>","https://www.zotero.org/groups/isicily/items/GRB3IPD5",{"type":157,"bibl":158},"discussion",[19],{"editor":160,"principal":162,"contributors":163,"change":179},{"_":161,"ref":102},"Jonathan Prag",{"_":161,"ref":102},[164,167,171,175],{"_":161,"xml:id":165,"ref":166},"JP","http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537",{"_":168,"xml:id":169,"ref":170},"James Cummings","JCu","http://orcid.org/0000-0002-6686-3728",{"_":172,"xml:id":173,"ref":174},"Simona Stoyanova","SS","https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3914-9569",{"_":176,"xml:id":177,"ref":178},"Valentina Mignosa","VM","https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7122-2511",{"_":180,"when":181,"who":102},"Jonathan Prag revised from autopsy notes and photographs","2026-02-18",{"n":106,"url":107,"height":108,"width":109,"desc":110,"surfaceType":111},[184,186],{"atLeast":185,"atMost":185},19,{"atLeast":187,"atMost":188},5,6,[190,191],"Supplementum epigraphicum graecum, 1923-","Manganaro, 1999, Sikelika: studi di antichità e di epigrafia della Sicilia greca",[193,194],"F2GG87EQ","GRB3IPD5",[196,197,198,21,27,31,199,200,201,202,200,203,204,130],"isic003501","fragment of a greek inscription",{"_":5},"syracusae","siracusa","sicilia","sicily","museo archeologico regionale paolo orsi","ancient greek",[],{"title":207,"body":208,"divs":209,"editions":234,"images":244,"handnote":255},"ISic003501. Fragment of a Greek inscription","\u003Cdiv id=\"editions\">\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Valentina Mignosa, Jonathan Prag; edition source: autopsy\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΝΙΚΑ \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΣΑ \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">.\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Valentina Mignosa, Jonathan Prag; edition source: autopsy\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΝΙΚΑ\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΣΑ\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">·\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003501_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2015-01-15\" src=\"ISic003501_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003501.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2015-01-15\" src=\"ISic003501-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003501_rear_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2015-01-15\" src=\"ISic003501_rear_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003501_rear.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2015-01-15\" src=\"ISic003501_rear-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text from autopsy\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"3\">3: \u003Cspan>Omitted by Manganaro\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2> translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The space below the letter A in line 2 is at least 10mm, and so much more than the interlineation of lines 1-2. If the text, as seems likely, is funerary, then the single stroke visible lower right, given its relative position, could well be the tail of a concluding hedera. Manganaro publishes this on the basis of a photograph he had previously taken of the fragment in the museum stores. As such, he speculatively restores it as a reference to a victory in a contest of some sort, by someone, son of [--]σας. Given the clear evidence that the fragment is a piece of marble in later re-use, and given the number of names that end in [---]νικα, it seems far more likely that this is a fragment of a funerary inscription from the second century CE or later.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> 49.1331.7 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Manganaro 1999 68-69 no.64 fig.146 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001813\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001813\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\">\u003Cp>Deep, simply v-cut letters, with pronounced terminal serifs.\u003C/p> Line 1-2  19  Interlineation line 1 to 2  5-6  \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv i